data.title: Super Tasty!
data.text:
First time eating there and definitely will go back! It's a small place with great atmosphere, well stocked bar, and attentive waitstaff.

My mojito was delicious, not too strong, not too sweet... really well balanced. I ordered the Pollo empanada appetizer and it was lovely, a little sweeter than anticipated but the tender chopped chicken mixed with raisins and olives was delightful and a nice size to share.

I of course ordered the Cuban sandwich. It was one of the best I have ever had. The bread had the perfect crisp to the outside and delicately soft on the inside, and the meats, cheese, pickle and sauce were nicely balanced.

I am looking forward to going back and trying more things on the menu.

data.title: Mojito-riffic
data.text: Still very good after all these years.  Best Mojito's around.  And how do you top a Cuban steak sandwich with fried onions and Swiss Cheese?  By putting french fries right on the sandwich!  Awesome.  Not as crowded as it used to be, which is not a bad thing.

data.title: Great food. Cafe atmosphere
data.text: Ate here with 3 coworkers while traveling on business based on a suggestion from a local. The staff was great - friendly and helpful. Food was awesome. Ambiance was comfortable but not fancy. The chicken empanadas are awesome though they sound a little unusual having raisins and olives. Everyone enjoyed their meals.

data.title: Quick bite to eat
data.text: Very friendly service. The waitress was very nice and totally accomodating. I had a salad with cuban chicken. Black bean soup was not hot. Red beans and rice were fantastic.

data.title: We came back for the plantain chips
data.text: We arrived at 4 pm. Only a few customers were eating. The last time we were here at 6:30 pm and it was packed. The plantain chips were as tasty as we remembered. My wife's salad was fresh and well presented and tasty. I had chicken flavored with citrus, yellow rice, and grilled veggies. All were tasty and the meal was well presented. Service was very good.

data.title: Food was ok
data.text: We went at lunch after visiting the museum. The meat in my sandwich was very dry and not flavorful which resulted in me drenching the sandwich in the sauce provided to make the roll and meat less chewy.

data.title: Cuban-ish
data.text: I have previously spent extensive time in Cuban areas of Florida, and was blessed to have many authentic Cuban restaurants nearby.  I was excited to try Cubanitas, but found it to be flavor.  The sandwich was not really pressed, the black beans were bland, etc.  I will try this restaurant out again, but will try other menu options...

data.title: Excellent food and service
data.text: If you like to have a real nice lunch, cuban food style, you can't miss this restaurant. As soon as you enter, you will be seated and the excellent service just begins. A large variety of food, very difficult to select, but just ask for suggestion, you will be pleased!

data.title: Not so Cuban
data.text: When to dinner with my wife on Tuesday. My wife had the Lechón Asado with yellow rice, I had the Ropa vieja with white rice and black beans. The yellow rice was not yellow more like orange. More like Mexican style.  The Mojito needed work did not taste like a Mojito. Don't know what happened use to have the best Mojitos in Milwaukee. Hopefully they go back to basics, just like Cuban food and drinks should be.

data.title: Pretty tasty Cuban food
data.text: Enjoyed the meal at this Cuban restaurant on a recent visit.  It has a pretty good menu and is known for its Mojito.  Mine was a little bitter for my liking.  Had the Ropa Vieja which is the shredded steak and it was excellent.  It was recommended by the staff.  Also had a side of empanadas and they were very good.  Good local spot for Cuban food!

data.title: Cuban in Milwaukee... about what you'd expect
data.text:
having lived in the Tampa area, and spent a lot of time in South Florida, I've had plenty of good Cuban food.. this was not it.
The empanadas were cold in the middle, as if they'd been micro-waved.
The Ropa Vieja, which is what I went in for, was not like any I had ever had before... it almost tasted like Ropa, but that's where the similarity ended. it was kind of bland, and too saucy.. it needed to be kicked up several notches.
Had I never had Cuban food in Florida this probably would have been good... even the empenada tasted pretty good, it was just cold in the middle....
The best I can say is.. meh.. I won't rush back there, but it could have been a lot worse.

data.title: Mojitos
data.text: We went for lunch on a Saturday.  The Cuban sandwich was good, though it could have used more pickles. The mojitos were very good.  Black bean soup and fried ripe plantains completed our selections.  We'd like to go back and try other menu selecctions.

data.title: Sandwiches will not disappoint
data.text: In the heart of downtown Milwaukee, Cubanitas serves traditional grilled/pressed sandwiches that will not disappoint.  They are known for their Cubans and plantain chips with guac.  Can't vouch for anything other than the sandwiches personally, but I go with people who order more meal-type things and everything looks and smells amazing.

data.title: Good food
data.text: Food was good. If you want Cuban food in Milwaukee. Only complaint: I ordered take out and they didn't include one of the dishes I'd ordered and paid for. I didn't check, and didn't realize till I was back at hotel. So check your order!

data.title: Way overpriced , mediocre service
data.text: Went for a late lunch during a weekday . We were the only people in the restaurant . The person in the bar tells us that during the day they don't have waiter service , so we order our food at the bar . The food was alright , although nothing spectacular ,with portions on the smaller side .  Considering what we had , the prices were really high . Won't be back .

data.title: Delicious!
data.text: I had my first dining experience at Cubainitas and it did not disappoint! I was with a couple friends so we were able to order a few things and share, which was really nice to try a couple different dishes. We started with mojitos and empanadas that were very tasty and not greasy at all. The mojitos were so refreshing and prepared with a perfect balance of mint, sweetness and of course rum! We then each ordered a different sandwich and shared. Everything was so good! At the end of the meal we ordered a caipirinha that also delicious! Another perfect balance of cachaca, lime, and sweetness!  Our server was very attentive and helpful when we had questions. We will definitely return!

data.title: I was disappointed
data.text: I was disappointed since I expected more from this highly rated restaurant. Perhaps the reason is that I've had much better Cuban food elsewhere including during a visit to Cuba. I also don't like restaurants that nickel and dime customers for extras like having the fish blackened. I would have also liked it more if the restaurant would have  had draft beer. Service was just fine. From my own observation, the place was very popular for social interactions among friends, but this isn't what I was looking for.

data.title: Great!
data.text: Awesome place for food, drinks and enjoying time with friends. Loved the empanadas, guacamole and mojitos! We've visited this bar multiple times during our business trip and enjoyed it more with each visit. Definitely recommended!

data.title: Yumm
data.text: I visited Cubanitas with my boyfriend and a friend a couple weekends ago on Saturday around 3pm and the restaurant was not very busy. We got a table right away and ordered our appetizer and our food which came out quickly. The waitresd was really nice and the raspberry ice  tea was delicious. We all ordered the Cuban sandwich which was good and the fries were awesome. It's a huge portion and I probably could have split it with someone and the prices are reasonable. I would go again.

data.title: Romantic spot for date night!
data.text: Cute spot with really romantic atmosphere for date night. Service was excellent. The gentleman who served us was funny and helpful. We ordered the empanadas, a cuban sandwich, fried yucca, and their daily special arroz con pollo (rice with chicken). All were fantastic. Empanadas were so good. Portions were generous! Our new favorite spot for Cuban.
